### User:
write a JavaScript program to generate and print out the ascii character and hexadecimal codes for 0 to 7f

### Response:


Here is an example of how you could write this in JavaScript:
```javascript
for (let i = 0; i <= 127; i++) {
    let asciiCode = String.fromCharCode(i);
    console.log(`ASCII code for ${asciiCode}: ` + `${i}`);
}

console.log("");
for (let i = 0x80; i <= 127; i++) {
    let hexCode = String.fromCharCode(i).toString(16);
    console.log(`Hex code for ${hexCode}: ` + `${i}`);
}
```This will output the ASCII and HEX codes for each character from 0 to 7f in two separate loops. The first loop uses a simple `for` statement with an index starting at 0, while the second loop starts at 80 (since characters above that are represented by multiple bytes). Each time through the loop, it converts the ASCII or HEX code of the character into a string and logs it to the console.
